# Admin right-rail experiences

## Layout

- Full-height panel docked to the **right** over `bg-black/40`.
- Solo: `fixed inset-0 z-50 flex justify-end` owns overlay + panel.
- Stacked follow-on (message, find vendor, etc.): parent owns overlay at `z-[55]`; each rail uses `panelOnly` + `stackedPosition`.

## Stacking rule

When an action opens a **second** rail (draft SMS, vendor search, etc.):

1. **Keep** the source review rail open — do not close it first.
2. Place the follow-on panel **left**, source review **right**.
3. Shared overlay dismisses the whole stack; follow-on close returns to source alone; source close dismisses both.
4. Match vendor assign (`FindExternalVendorRail` + `SlaOverdueActionRail`) and lease incentive (`LeaseRenewalIncentiveMessageRail` + `LeaseRenewalEscalatedRail`).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — replace review with follow-on
closeLeaseRenewalRail()
setIncentiveBrief(brief)

// ✅ GOOD — stack beside review
setIncentiveBrief(brief)
// parent: stackedPosition left = message, right = review
```

## Chrome (keep consistent)

Use `adminRightRailPanelClass` / `adminRightRailStackRoundedClass` from `@/lib/adminRightRail`.

- Border `#e5e7eb`, white bg, shadow `0px_8px_24px_rgba(0,0,0,0.12)`
- Width `max-w-[min(100vw,520px)]` or `560px` for denser review rails
- Solo / left stack: `rounded-l-[12px]`; right stack: `rounded-none border-l-0`
- Close: `absolute right-4 top-4`; title ~`text-[20px] font-semibold`; body scroll `min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-y-auto`
- Escape / overlay: skip when `panelOnly` (parent handles); block dismiss while `saving`/`sending`

## Props every stackable rail needs

`panelOnly?: boolean`, `stackedPosition?: 'left' | 'right'` — when `panelOnly`, return the panel only (no overlay, no Escape listener).
